# Cloudflare Pages _headers — defence-in-depth for the SPA origin.
#
# The localStorage nsec persistence (see lib/stores/session.ts) makes any
# same-origin script read full account control. The actual Content-
# Security-Policy is now emitted by SvelteKit as a <meta http-equiv> tag
# at build time (see kit.csp in svelte.config.js) — that path can hash
# our inline bootstrap scripts so we don't have to fall back to
# 'unsafe-inline'. Setting CSP here too creates a duplicate-policy
# situation that's confusing to debug and hash-incompatible (CF Pages
# doesn't know about the build-time hashes), so this file owns just
# the non-CSP security headers.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: interest-cohort=(), browsing-topics=()
  X-Frame-Options: DENY

# NIP-05 verification: clients fetch /.well-known/nostr.json from any
# origin to check that <name>@<domain> resolves to the claimed pubkey.
# Without CORS, the cross-origin XHR fails and the verification badge
# stays grey. Content-Type explicit so CF Pages doesn't sniff to
# octet-stream (which some clients would treat as a verification fail).
/.well-known/nostr.json
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Content-Type: application/json
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300
